# Browser-Only Task DAG: Ungoogled Chromium To Echothink Browser

## Summary

This DAG converts the current Ungoogled Chromium patch/config repo into a Windows-first Echothink Browser Alpha. It includes only browser-side work: patch structure, branding, defaults, New Tab, bundled extension, Side Panel modes, login gate, device identity, request proof helper, optional `echo://`, Windows packaging, and validation.

Backend services are out of scope; browser tasks may define request shapes and route contracts only where needed for the browser implementation.

## Public Browser Interfaces

- Patch namespace: `patches/echothink/`, appended after inherited patches in `patches/series`.
- Extension package: `extensions/echothink-workspace/`.
- Side Panel modes: `chat` and `workspace_context`, persisted per profile.
- Chat scope metadata: `current_page`, `project`, `app_domain`, `task_wave`, `artifacts`, `organization`.
- Local device metadata: `device_id`, `installation_id`, `browser_channel`, `browser_version`, `enrollment_status`, `last_verified_at`.
- Extension bridge APIs: `getDeviceStatus`, `requestEnrollmentChallenge`, `signProofPayload`, `clearEnrollment`.
- Default routes: New Tab `https://app.echothink.ai/newtab`, search `https://search.echothink.ai/search?q={searchTerms}`, suggest `https://search.echothink.ai/suggest?q={searchTerms}`.

